The paper discusses the characterization and computation of policies for families of problems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and planning (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of trajectory constraints, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction of generalized planning to fully observable non-deterministic planning, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
